<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="43" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d43">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/7608</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-24">
                                    <hi rend="italic">24 October, 1917</hi>
                                </date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: Thank you for sending
                            me Mr. Phillips’ memorandum about the question put by Mr. de
                                Laboulaye.<note n="47" xml:id="d43fn1">
                                <ref target="frus1917Supp02v01#pg_696">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1917, supp. 2, vol.
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 696</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>I think that it would be a mistake for the British and French Governments
                            to address the Japanese Government with the request that Japan should
                            send troops to the West Front next spring and summer, but, of course, I
                            do not wish to press the objection and think it would be unwise to raise
                            one.</p>
                        <p>Cordially and sincerely yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>